  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The daily mortality was approximately between 200 and 500-- 200, 300.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the camp, in the B2B camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This-- I was always capable and able to give something, get something to Eva, who lived in a different block, or to my or Eva's parents.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I succeeded to shield both of the father and father-in-law, that they didn't have to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eva worked with children in the children's block, which was, again-- it wasn't a Potemkin's village.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a double Potemkin's village.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then one day, I proclaimed to somebody that I am trained as a male nurse.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And through a fluke, I got myself to the hospital block.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were three blocks which were hospital compounds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was working as a male orderly, or a nurse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They took everybody who was sick and put him there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the kind of German preciseness, or the German kind of absurd punctuality, there were people who were waiting for their death.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were dying like flies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had to get special kinds of ration, and special kind of bread.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they were getting white bread instead of the bread which we were-- sorry, we got also, each one of us, a piece of bread every day, which was a dark, military bread, which was not bad.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I still somehow like the bread-- for it has got a certain kind of trace of memory.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these sick people, who are just this sick, simply they got special kind of white, piece of white bread, which is not unlike like a big, bloated kind of the white French bread we have got here.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
